# gcloud builds submit upload-context exclusions.
#
# Without this file, gcloud falls back to .gitignore — but .gitignore excludes
# `dungeons/user/*`, which would strip out the kodiak runner from the build
# context and break the Dockerfile COPY step. So this file overrides.
#
# Rule: include EVERYTHING the Dockerfile needs to COPY at build time
# (index.js, types.d.ts, lib/, scripts/, dungeons/user/kodiak/, package*.json).
# Exclude everything else to keep the upload small + fast.

# ── always exclude ──
.git
.gitignore
.gcloudignore
node_modules/
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.log
*.bak

# ── secrets ──
.env
env.yml

# ── tests, coverage, temp ──
tests/coverage/
tmp/
.tmp/
data/
logs/
duckdb_temp_*
*scratch*

# ── docs / dev artifacts (NOT shipped to runtime) ──
docs/
plans/
research/
verification/
examples/
PHASE1-IMPROVEMENTS.md
LOGBOOK.md
CHANGELOG.md
README.md
HOOKS.md

# ── dungeons NOT used by kodiak runner ──
# kodiak's Dockerfile only COPYs `dungeons/user/kodiak/`, so other dungeon
# directories are useless bytes in the upload context. Excluded by directory.
# (Avoiding the `dungeons/user/` + `!dungeons/user/kodiak/` re-include trick
# because gitignore-style negation can't undo a parent-directory exclusion
# in all gcloud client versions.)
dungeons/customers/
dungeons/capstone/
dungeons/technical/
dungeons/vertical/
dungeons/*ai-dungeon*

# ── catch-all ignore prefix ──
ignore*

# ── exclude generated artifacts that exist in the kodiak dir ──
dungeons/user/kodiak/chunk-plan.json
dungeons/user/kodiak/validate.sql
dungeons/user/kodiak/examples/
